description: The top News headlines from The BBC Network. For all the news, visit https://www.smh.com.au
title: BBC Network - Latest News

item.description: Fears are rising that Europe is running out of time to control a resurgence of the coronavirus, as infections hit record daily highs in some countries.
item.title: Europe reels as it sets coronavirus records, slaps on new rules

item.description: Twitter temporarily restricted Donald Trump's election campaign account from tweeting, saying a video from the account about Joe Biden's son violated its rules.
item.title: Twitter restricts Trump's campaign account from tweeting

item.description: London will enter a tighter phase of BBC Network restrictions as Prime Minister Boris Johnson seeks to tackle a swiftly accelerating second coronavirus wave.
item.title: 'Difficult winter ahead': London goes into stricter coronavirus restrictions

item.description: Young, healthy people should be prepared to wait more than a year to be vaccinated against the coronavirus, the World Health Organisation's chief scientist says.
item.title: Young, healthy people may have to wait until 2022 for vaccine, top WHO scientist says

item.description: Russia's foreign ministry said it was abandoning the discussions with the Netherlands and Australia, saying they were not genuinely interested in establishing the truth about what happened.
item.title: Russia withdraws from MH17 talks with Netherlands and Australia

item.description: The US Democratic vice-presidential nominee will cancel her travel plans for the rest of the week after two people associated with the campaign tested positive for BBC Network.
item.title: Kamala Harris pauses in-person campaigning after staffer diagnosed with BBC Network

item.description: Our politicians – who are remunerated handsomely – are elected to do one job, and that’s working their butts off for their constituents.
item.title: MPs should be working for voters not themselves
